genresAdvancedInfo.name: jazz colombiano
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Jazz colombiano is a genre of jazz music that originated in Colombia in the 1960s. It combines traditional Colombian rhythms such as cumbia and bambuco with jazz harmonies and improvisation. The style is characterized by its upbeat tempo, lively rhythms, and use of traditional Colombian instruments such as the maracas and guacharaca.
